  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN193.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">poruḷvalitta talaimaka ṉeñciṟkuc collic celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How HE prevented going by speaking to [his] heart that coveted wealth.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN193.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>kāṉuyar maruṅkiṟ kavalai yallatu</l>
        <l>vāṉam vēṇṭā villē ruḻavar</l>
        <l>perunāḷ vēṭṭaṅ kiḷaiyeḻa vāytta</l>
        <l>porukaḷat tuḻanta kurutic cevvāyp</l>
        <l>poṟitta pōlum vāṉiṟa verutti</l>
        <l>ṉaṇinta pōluñ ceñcevic cēval</l>
        <l>kuṟumpoṟai yeḻunta neṭuntāḷ yāat</l>
        <l>taruṅkavaṭ ṭuyarciṉaip piḷḷai yūṭṭa</l>
        <l>viraintuvāy vaḻukkiya koḻuṅka ṇūṉṟaṭi</l>
        <l>tolpaci mutunari valci yāruñ</l>
        <l>curamek keḷiya maṉṉē naṉmaṉaip</l>
        <l>paṉmāṇ ṭaṅkiya cāya liṉmoḻi</l>
        <l>muruntēr muṟuva liḷaiyōḷ</l>
        <l>peruntō ḷiṉṟuyil kaiviṭu kalaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>Easy for us indeed are the deserts, (11a-c)</l>
        <l>where the old jackal with ancient hunger becomes full on the food (10)</l>
        <l>of meat pieces with eyes of fat that slipped in haste from the beaks (9)</l>
        <l>of the male birds with ears so red that they seem to be decorated (6)</l>
        <l>[and] neck of a colour so white that they seem to be imprinted(?), (5)</l>
        <l>[their] beaks red with the blood that was borne by the battlefield (4)</l>
        <l>that was attained when (3d)</l>
        <l>the ploughmen with bows as ploughs who do not need the sky, (2)</l>
        <l>but only the crossroads on the high sides of the forest, (1)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">rose with [their] kin for the great daily hunt, (3a-c)</l>
        <l>so as to feed [its] young ones in the high branches with difficult forks (8)</l>
        <l>of the long-trunked Yāam tree that rose on the short hillock. (7)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
